AB  - The purpose of this paper is to show how the Brecher-Diaz (1977) and Minabe (1974) propositions on the capital inflow from a tariff apply symmetrically to capital outflow. That is, when the home country continues to import the labor-intensive goods while remaining incompletely specialized, the capital outflow must reduce the home-country's real income. This will be so when the net return to home capital is greater than the home value of its marginal product at internal prices, but less than the home value of its marginal product at world prices.
