UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0022199681900441
AB  - This paper analyzes the role of monetary expansion in a two-country, two-sector model of accumulation. In addition, the model permits trade in securities and allows for feedback effects due to the variability of the terms of trade, and the world interest rate. It is shown that many of the results in small-country or other simpler models no longer hold. For instance, the neutrality of the saving rate implied by the small-country assumption no longer exists. It is now possible to choose combinations of the saving rate and the rate of monetary expansion to attain certain goals.
